{"FUN":[{"def":"Sport; merriment; frolicsome amusement.","pos":""}],"FUNAMBULATE":[{"def":"To walk or to dance on a rope.","pos":""}],"FUNAMBULATORY":[{"def":"Performing like a ropedancer.","pos":""},{"def":"Narrow, like the walk of a ropedancer.","pos":""}],"FUNAMBULIST":[{"def":"A ropewalker or ropedancer.","pos":""},{"def":"A ropewalker or ropedancer.","pos":""}],"FUNCTION":[{"def":"The appropriate action of any special organ or part of an animal or vegetable organism; as, the function of the heart or the limbs; the function of leaves, sap, roots, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"A quantity so connected with another quantity, that if any alteration be made in the latter there will be a consequent alteration in the former.","pos":""}],"FUNCTIONAL":[{"def":"Pertaining to the function of an organ or part, or to the functions in general.","pos":""}],"FUNCTIONALIZE":[{"def":"To assign to some function or office.","pos":""}],"FUNCTIONALLY":[{"def":"In a functional manner; as regards normal or appropriate activity.","pos":""}],"FUNCTIONARY":[{"def":"One charged with the performance of a function or office; as, a public functionary; secular functionaries.","pos":""}],"FUNCTIONLESS":[{"def":"Destitute of function, or of an appropriate organ.","pos":""}],"FUND":[{"def":"The stock of a national debt; public securities; evidences (stocks or bonds) of money lent to government, for which interest is paid at prescribed intervals; -- called also public funds.","pos":""}],"FUNDABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being funded, or converted into a fund; convertible into bonds.","pos":""}],"FUNDAMENT":[{"def":"The part of the body on which one sits; the buttocks; specifically (Anat.","pos":""}],"FUNDAMENTAL":[{"def":"Pertaining to the foundation or basis; serving for the foundation.","pos":""}],"FUNDAMENTALLY":[{"def":"Primarily; originally; essentially; radically; at the foundation; in origin or constituents.","pos":""}],"FUNDED":[{"def":"Existing in the form of bonds bearing regular interest; as, funded debt.","pos":""},{"def":"Invested in public funds; as, funded money.","pos":""}],"FUNDHOLDER":[{"def":"One who has money invested in the public funds.","pos":""}],"FUNDING":[{"def":"Providing a fund for the payment of the interest or principal of a debt.","pos":""},{"def":"Investing in the public funds.","pos":""}],"FUNDLESS":[{"def":"Destitute of funds.","pos":""}],"FUNDUS":[{"def":"The bottom or base of any hollow organ; as, the fundus of the bladder; the fundus of the eye.","pos":""}],"FUNEBRIAL":[{"def":"Pertaining to a funeral or funerals; funeral; funereal.","pos":""}],"FUNERAL":[{"def":"The solemn rites used in the disposition of a dead human body, whether such disposition be by interment, burning, or otherwise; esp.","pos":""},{"def":"The procession attending the burial of the dead; the show and accompaniments of an interment.","pos":""}],"FUNERATE":[{"def":"To bury with funeral rites.","pos":""}],"FUNERATION":[{"def":"The act of burying with funeral rites.","pos":""}],"FUNEREAL":[{"def":"Suiting a funeral; pertaining to burial; solemn.","pos":""}],"FUNEST":[{"def":"Lamentable; doleful.","pos":""}],"FUNGAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to fungi.","pos":""}],"FUNGATE":[{"def":"A salt of fungic acid.","pos":""}],"FUNGE":[{"def":"A blockhead; a dolt; a fool.","pos":""}],"FUNGI IMPERFECTI":[{"def":"A heterogenous group of fungi of which the complete life history is not known.","pos":""}],"FUNGIA":[{"def":"A genus of simple, stony corals; -- so called because they are usually flat and circular, with radiating plates, like the gills of a mushroom.","pos":""}],"FUNGIAN":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to the Fungidæ, a family of stony corals.","pos":""},{"def":"One of the Fungidæ.","pos":""}],"FUNGIBLES":[{"def":"Things which may be furnished or restored in kind, as distinguished from specific things; -- called also fungible things.","pos":""},{"def":"Movable goods which may be valued by weight or measure, in contradistinction from those which must be judged of individually.","pos":""}],"FUNGIC":[{"def":"Pertaining to, or obtained from, mushrooms; as, fungic acid.","pos":""}],"FUNGICIDE":[{"def":"Anything that kills fungi.","pos":""}],"FUNGIFORM":[{"def":"Shaped like a fungus or mushroom.","pos":""}],"FUNGILLIFORM":[{"def":"Shaped like a small fungus.","pos":""}],"FUNGIN":[{"def":"A name formerly given to cellulose found in certain fungi and mushrooms.","pos":""}],"FUNGITE":[{"def":"A fossil coral resembling Fungia.","pos":""}],"FUNGIVOROUS":[{"def":"Eating fungi; -- said of certain insects and snails.","pos":""}],"FUNGOID":[{"def":"Like a fungus; fungous; spongy.","pos":""}],"FUNGOSITY":[{"def":"The quality of that which is fungous; fungous excrescence.","pos":""}],"FUNGOUS":[{"def":"Of the nature of fungi; spongy.","pos":""},{"def":"Growing suddenly, but not substantial or durable.","pos":""}],"FUNGUS":[{"def":"Any one of the Fungi, a large and very complex group of thallophytes of low organization, -- the molds, mildews, rusts, smuts, mushrooms, toadstools, puff balls, and the allies of each.","pos":""},{"def":"A spongy, morbid growth or granulation in animal bodies, as the proud flesh of wounds.","pos":""}],"FUNICLE":[{"def":"The little stalk that attaches a seed to the placenta.","pos":""}],"FUNICULAR":[{"def":"Pertaining to a funiculus; made up of, or resembling, a funiculus, or funiculi; as, a funicular ligament.","pos":""}],"FUNICULATE":[{"def":"Forming a narrow ridge.","pos":""}],"FUNICULUS":[{"def":"Bryozoa, and Phylactolema.","pos":""}],"FUNILIFORM":[{"def":"Resembling a cord in toughness and flexibility, as the roots of some endogenous trees.","pos":""}],"FUNIS":[{"def":"A cord; specifically, the umbilical cord or navel string.","pos":""}],"FUNK":[{"def":"An offensive smell; a stench.","pos":""}],"FUNKY":[{"def":"Pertaining to, or characterized by, great fear, or funking.","pos":""}],"FUNNEL":[{"def":"A vessel of the shape of an inverted hollow cone, terminating below in a pipe, and used for conveying liquids into a close vessel; a tunnel.","pos":""},{"def":"A passage or avenue for a fluid or flowing substance; specifically, a smoke flue or pipe; the iron chimney of a steamship or the like.","pos":""}],"FUNNELFORM":[{"def":"Having the form of a funnel, or tunnel; that is, expanding gradually from the bottom upward, as the corolla of some flowers; infundibuliform.","pos":""}],"FUNNY":[{"def":"Droll; comical; amusing; laughable.","pos":""}]}